TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi beforefieldinit StandardCommands extends System.Object

Docs.summary: Defines identifiers for the standard set of commands that are available to most applications.

remarks.format:
## Remarks This class defines <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> identifiers for standard commands that are available to designers.
To add a command from the StandardCommands class to a designer menu, you must call the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IMenuCommandService.AddCommand%2A> method of an <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IMenuCommandService> and add a <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.MenuCommand> that contains a <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> from StandardCommands.
## Examples The following code example illustrates how to add a member of the StandardCommands class to a <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.MenuCommand> and how to add the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.MenuCommand> to an <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IMenuCommandService>.
[!code-cpp[MenuCommand Example#1](~/add/codesnippet/cpp/t-system.componentmodel._163_1.cpp)] [!code-cs[MenuCommand Example#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.componentmodel._163_1.cs)] [!code-vb[MenuCommand Example#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.componentmodel._163_1.vb)]

MemberSignature.Value: public static readonly System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID VerbFirst;
.field public static initonly class System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID VerbFirst

Docs.summary: Gets the first of a set of verbs. This field is read-only.

remarks.format:
## Remarks This is a special <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> that identifies the first of a set of designer verbs.
The Visual Studio Windows Forms Designer automatically maps designer verbs to the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IDesigner.Verbs%2A> property on <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.IDesigner>, so generally you do not need to access this command.
All designer verbs for an object become commands with a <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.CommandID> within a sequential range of IDs that begins with VerbFirst and ends with <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.StandardCommands.VerbLast>.
